    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 574.C1/112a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You are instructed to take up the matter of the adhesion of the Republic of
                    Panama to the International Radio Telegraph Convention of London and to press
                    the matter actively in the endeavor to have this agreement ratified as soon as
                    possible, on account of the early opening of the Panama Canal to traffic. Report
                    by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
